    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nAfter #38475, `require(\"vim.treesitter._select\").select_parent`, or more precisely `visual_select`, selects the entire line if you previously left a Visual Line selection.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nnvim --clean\n:e test.lua\n:lua vim.treesitter.start()\nw\nV<esc>\n:lua require(\"vim.treesitter._select\").select_parent(vim.v.count1)\n\ntest.lua\n```\nlocal api = vim.api\n\nlocal bufnr = api.nvim_get_current_buf()\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nIn the example it should expand and select only the `api`.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0-dev-2727+gad4bc2d90c\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nWindows 10\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nNeovide\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nN/A\n\n### Installation\n\nnightly release: nvim-win64.zip",
